      "side": 1,
      "message": "In isolation, I would usually prefer once-used strings to be inline. I defined kBeginMessage as a static variable here in order to be consistent with kAbortMesssage (and because there should be no performance/behavioral difference). If all our messages were only used once, I might\u0027ve used them all inline. I don\u0027t think there\u0027s a strict one-way-or-the-other rule. I would try/imagine both and use whichever approach I think reads most consistently and easily.",
